# Summary
This documentation explains how Amplitude identifies unique users through a system of three IDs (Device ID, User ID, and Amplitude ID), detailing how these IDs are assigned in various scenarios and how Amplitude merges users when it determines multiple Amplitude IDs belong to the same user, with important considerations for cross-domain tracking and data consistency.

